  "prompt": "How do founders deal with student loans and other obligations?",
  "response": "Founders often deal with student loans and other financial obligations through various strategies:\n\n1. Income-based repayment plans\n- Federal student loan programs offering flexible payments\n- Payments based on current income levels\n\n2. Refinancing options\n- Consolidating loans at lower interest rates\n- Negotiating more favorable repayment terms\n\n3. Part-time work or consulting\n- Maintaining side income to cover loan payments\n- Supplementing startup funding\n\n4. Bootstrapping\n- Minimizing personal expenses\n- Living frugally during startup phase\n\n5. Family support\n- Temporary housing with family\n- Financial assistance from relatives\n\n6. Startup funding strategies\n- Using initial funding to cover personal expenses\n- Paying themselves modest salaries\n\n7. Deferment or forbearance\n- Temporarily pausing student loan payments\n- Exploring hardship options\n\n8. Startup-specific loan programs\n- Specialized financing for entrepreneurs\n- Grants and low-interest startup loans\n\n9. Equity compensation\n- Offering equity instead of high salaries\n- Aligning team compensation with startup growth\n\n10. Seeking investor understanding\n- Being transparent about personal financial obligations\n- Demonstrating financial management skills\n\nEach founder's approach depends on individual circumstances and startup stage.",
